<section xml:id="sec-integral-solutions" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Integrals as Solutions</title>

  <introduction>
<p>
  Differential equations in the form <m>\frac{dy}{dx} = f(x)</m> can be solved simply by integrating.
  One particular application of this is to acceleration and velocity questions.
</p>
  </introduction>

